description.undefined: The top-level permit ontology contains the relevant terminology related to permitting processes. Based on Semantic Modelling and Linking (SML, EN 17632),  it contains the core terminology for DigiChecks services to communicate unambiguously about a permitting process.

labels.undefined: Permit ontology based on the SML framework

definition.value: Concept that forms a manifestation and a demarcation in a concrete space-time, and which has a certain state at any moment in time. An entity has a unique identity that remains constant throughout its life cycle. The life cycle of an entity is made up of the sequence of states of that entity, which follow each other in time. An entity is an object or an activity. An object exists, an activity takes place
The objectification of a value of a quality having a complex value like a simple value sec combined with other metadata or just a combination of simple values
The objectification of a reference for a relation having a complex value like a simple reference sec combined with other metadata or just a combination of simple references (n-ary relation)
A meta-concept having concepts as instances that can have attributes or relations
That which represents something else
Temporal part of an entity during a period between two events. A state is characterized by the properties and relations of the entity
A Verification is an activity that checks if a subject is compliant with a requirement.
Concept that forms a manifestation and demarcation in an abstract space. An abstract concept has no life cycle
A decision is an activity of making a choice or judgement based on the available resources.

A set of instructions or guidelines that are structured in a format that can be easily interpreted and processed by a computer or software program. The term "rule" refers here to checking rules specifically and is not to be confused with inferencing rules for deriving knowledge.
An explicit relation between subject and requirement that shows that the subject needs to fulfill the stated requirement.
Named concept, which forms an actual or virtual demarcation in a concrete (physical, three-dimensional) space, which we experience in reality
A meta-concept which instances are concepts (not individuals)
Concept that forms a manifestation and a demarcation in a concrete space-time. A concrete concept has a life cycle
A requirement that is specific to projects / use case. It cannot be generalized over multiple projects / use cases.

The objectification of a value of a quantity (typically involving a quantity kind and a unit) having a complex value like a simple value sec combined with other metadata or just a combination of simple values
A permit is a written permission or authorisation delivered by a competent authority, entity, or person, that is legally delegated to allow someone to do something or to go somewhere.
Object which describes a thing in reality
An entity that does not yet exist in physical reality, but which exists in mental or conceptual reality
An entity concerned with technical properties and relations that implements or plays functional entities
An entity involving the external behavior where the output contributes to stakeholder objectives implemented/played by one or more technical entities
An entity that exists or has existed in the physical reality
Any quantity of land capable of being described with such definiteness that its locations and boundaries may be established.
The most generic concept
Entity that exists or can exist within a concrete space-time. An object executes an activity, and is transformed by an activity

label.en: A rule based on triple (subject, predicate, object) pattern.

definition.value: An attribute (quality or quantity) or relation represented as an individual defined by a concept
Entity that takes place or can take place in a concrete space-time. An activity transforms objects, and is executed by an object
Transition between two successive states of an entity (object or activity). An event is triggered in a state
A requirement that is not specific for any projects / use case.
A rule that should hold for something, defined via its attributes or relations
A rule that should hold for something, defined via its attributes or relations
A meta-concept having concepts as instances having no further attributes or relations (annotations only)
One of the four fundamental states of matter being a solid, liquid, gas or plasma
Any observable property that can be measured and quantified numerically
The entity aspect a requirement applies to
The type of source from which a requirement comes like a client, by definition, recommended by the sector or demanded by law/regulation
The type of thing being transferred, here: material, information, energy or force
A particular quantity value that has been chosen as a scale for measuring other quantities the same kind
The seriousness of a requirement like demanded or wished
A set of procedures to check if the subject is compliant with requirement.
A permit request is a written appeal or application made to obtain official approval for something from a designated authority.
A temporary process undertaken to solve a well-defined goal or objective with clearly defined start and end times, a set of clearly defined tasks, and a budget.
A piece of written, printed, or electronic matter that provides information or evidence or that serves as an official record or acts as a reference.

note.value: Geometry can be used as a representation of the shape, extent or location of a Feature and may exist as a self-contained entity.

definition.value: A coherent set of direct positions in space. The positions are held within a Spatial Reference System (SRS).
Object that exists or may exist within physical 4D space-time. A physical object forms a manifestation and a demarcation of matter and/or energy, and is (in)directly perceptible by the senses
Indicates the relation between a request and the specific permit it was requesting.
A decomposition (hasPart) relation between concrete concepts
The preferred lexical label for a resource, in a given language.

comment.en: A resource has no more than one value of skos:prefLabel per language tag, and no more than one value of skos:prefLabel without language tag.

definition.value: Is an association that indicates that the object has been derived in the source object.
Indicates the link between location and parcel.
Indicates the link from a project to a / multiple permit requests.
Indicates the relation between a permit and the related request for it
Indicates the link between a permit and corresponding permit request that are / were made to obtain certain permit
Provides the possibility to indicate if certain conditions are complementary (AND) or supplementary (OR).

Is a relation between a single thing and a plurality that indicates that the collected object is element of the collection of objects, under the constraint that the element may not be the same object as the plural object. In other words a collection cannot be an element of itself.
Is an involvement in an occurrence that indicates that the involved object has a role as performer of the occurrence.
Is an involvement in an occurrence that indicates that the involved object has a role as controller of the occurrence.
Is an association that indicates a method to verify if the verification object has a method linked to it.
Is an association that indicates that the representer object represents the represented object.
Relation to check if the address is linked to a location.
Indicates that a / multiple verifications where carried out as a foundation for certain decision taken.
Is a relation that indicates the involved object has a origin or source from another object.
Is a relation indicating the choice or judgment made based on available resources.
The (unstructured) requirement for something
Is a relation that determines how an object is represented similar to a target object
Indicates that a permit request was made by appropriate associated person / organization that is authorized to make the specific request.
Is an involvement in an occurrence that indicates that the involved object has been operated upon by the occurrence.
Provides a list of possible decision outcomes which impact the permit request.

Relation that is used to indicate that a concept was linked to certain resource in the past. this is meant to keep track of different versions of resources, keep history on all links ever made from concept to resource.
Relation that is used to link various concepts to a resource. Many concepts require to be linked to certain proof documents / descriptions. This relation is set on Top Concept level.
The information object that describes something

Is a conceptual requirement for compliancy to a criterion that indicates that a member of the class shall be conformant to a qualitative requirement. Typically an item, story or document of a kind that should be conform to the content of a document.
Indicates in what capacity someone/something is linked to a project, permit, ...
Indicates that a parcel is located at a certain location.
Is an association to ensure that the involved object has an allocation to the corresponding requirement.
A spatial representation for a given Feature.
Indicates that a geometry has a location linked to it.
